173. -To the Archdeacon of Barnstaple.-—-The Bishop had been informed that the Cemetery of the Church of BARNSTAPLE had been polluted by bloodshed, during a fight between two of the parishioners, Ralph Symon and Richard Warnes. The Archdeacon was to investigate the case ; and, if he found that the said cemetery had been polluted as alleged, he was to forbid all interments therein until it should have been reconciled.— Dated at Faringdon (Hants), 23 Dec.
